4.jpg"></p>
<p class=3D"paraNoIndent1">When trying to understand the current business p=
rocesses we will probably draw a set of =E2=80=98as-is=E2=80=99 business pr=
ocess models (see <a href=3D"https://learning.oreilly.com/library/view/mode=
lling-business-information/9781780173535/15_ch01.xhtml#fig1.5">Figure 1.5</=
a>). We will then draw a series of =E2=80=98to-be=E2=80=99 business process=
 models and discuss those with the business.</p>
<p class=3D"figcap" id=3D"fig1.5">Figure 1.5 A business process model</p>
<p class=3D"centerImage"><img src=3D"https://learning.oreilly.com/library/v=
iew/modelling-business-information/9781780173535/images/fig1.5.jpg" style=
=3D"width: 100%;" alt=3D"image" width=3D"1415" height=3D"888" data-mfp-src=
